label.value: deubiquitinase activity

value.value: An isopeptidase activity that cleaves ubiquitin from a target protein to which it is conjugated.

definition.value: There are two main classes of deubiquitinating enzymes: cysteine proteases (i.e., thiol dependent) and metalloproteases.

label.value: regulation of mitotic DNA replication initiation from late origin

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of firing from a late origin of replication involved in mitotic DNA replication.

label.value: nucleolar exosome (RNase complex)

value.value: A ribonuclease complex that has 3-prime to 5-prime distributive hydrolytic exoribonuclease activity and in some taxa (e.g. yeast) endoribonuclease activity, producing 5-prime-phosphomonoesters. Participates in a multitude of cellular RNA processing and degradation events preventing nuclear export and/or translation of aberrant RNAs. Restricted to processing linear and circular single-stranded RNAs (ssRNA) only. RNAs with complex secondary structures may have to be unwound or pre-processed by co-factors prior to entering the complex, esp if the 3-prime end is structured.

label.value: mitotic nuclear membrane organization

value.value: A mitotic cell cycle process which results in the assembly, arrangement, or disassembly of the nuclear inner or outer membrane during mitosis.

definition.value: This process only occurs in organisms which undergo 'closed mitosis' without nuclear breakdown.

label.value: nuclear membrane biogenesis

value.value: The process in which a nuclear membrane is synthesized, aggregates, and bonds together.

label.value: mitotic nuclear membrane biogenesis

value.value: A process in which the nuclear inner or outer membrane is synthesized, aggregates, and bonds together during mitotic nuclear division.

label.value: cellular response to environmental stimulus

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an environmental stimulus.

label.value: tRNA (guanine-N7)-methylation

value.value: The process whereby a guanine in a tRNA is methylated at the N7 position of guanine.

label.value: cytoskeletal protein-membrane anchor activity

value.value: The binding activity of a molecule that brings together a cytoskeletal protein or protein complex and a plasma membrane lipid or membrane-associated protein, in order to maintain the localization of the cytoskeleton at a specific cortical membrane location.

label.value: microtubule anchoring at cell cortex of cell tip

value.value: Any process in which a microtubule is maintained in a specific location at the cell tip by attachment to the cell cortex.

label.value: regulation of protein localization to medial cortex

value.value: Any process that regulates the localization of a protein to the medial cortex.

label.value: positive regulation of protein localization to medial cortex

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to the medial cortex.

label.value: regulation of cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the cellular response to osmotic stress.

label.value: formin-nucleated actin cable organization

value.value: A process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a formin-nucleated actin cable.

label.value: protein localization to P-body

value.value: Any process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a P-body.

label.value: regulation of actomyosin structure organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures containing both actin and myosin or paramyosin.

label.value: positive regulation of mitotic spindle organization

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mitotic spindle organization.

label.value: negative regulation of meiosis I

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of meiosis I, a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the first phase of meiosis, in which cells divide and homologous chromosomes are paired and segregated from each other, producing two daughter cells.

label.value: regulation of G2/MI transition of meiotic cell cycle

value.value: Any signaling pathway that modulates the activity of a cell cycle cyclin-dependent protein kinase to modulate the switch from G2 phase to MI phase of the meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: negative regulation of G2/MI transition of meiotic cell cycle

label.value: positive regulation of G2/MI transition of meiotic cell cycle

label.value: meiotic actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cytoskeletal structure composed of actin filaments, myosin, and myosin-associated proteins that forms beneath the plasma membrane of many cells, including animal cells and yeast cells, in a plane perpendicular to the axis of the meiotic spindle, i.e. the cell division plane. Ring contraction is associated with centripetal growth of the membrane that divides the cytoplasm of the two future daughter cells. In animal cells, the meiotic contractile ring is located inside the plasma membrane at the location of the cleavage furrow. In fungal cells, the meiotic contractile ring forms beneath the plasma membrane of the prospore envelope in preparation for completing cytokinesis.
